job description
3m is seeking a data science engineer for the corporate research process laboratory located in woodbury mn
job summary
the data scientist in the measurement and inspection systems group in 3m corporate research process laboratory is responsible for providing data analytics technique to sensor system lab and manufacturing process and product the measurement and inspection systems group is responsible for designing developing and integrating novel inspection and measurement technology for 3m manufacturing and process product development this position requires working with multi-disciplinary team and the ability to analyze a diverse range of data set the candidate will have a high degree of initiative to develop and execute a project plan and must have the ability to identify and propose new project opportunity and set direction for creating a technology platform based on data analytics the data scientist position will contribute to the development of new measurement and inspection capability in support of the complete range of 3m product and process the candidate must have superior inter-personnel skill be able to inspire and motivate team member and influence the invention of new technology that impact 3m business
primary responsibilities include but are not limited to the following
provide and or develop cutting edge data analytics such a predictive modeling statistic machine learning data mining and other data analysis technique to collect explore and extract insight from structured and unstructured data other relevant area may include signal processing sensor and electronics probabilistic inference and or computational statistic 3d computer vision acquisition segmentation registration classification deep learning analysis and reduction of high-dimensional data
lead project in machine learning data mining signal processing sensor and electronics probabilistic inference and or computational statistic
query database extract raw data develop and implement data transforms and analysis
create highly custom algorithm seeking to capitalize on value in various datasets image time series and multivariate input implement relevant and valuable computational algorithm in software that support 3m business
collaborate with a team of physicist engineer chemist on both theoretical and practical project that will use his her scientific mathematical and computational skill to drive new-to-the-world technology development and introduction
provide strong understanding of internal business segment stakeholder and posse strong written and communication skill present result in a clear and concise manner to multidisciplinary team and management making recommendation for change and extending capability by implementing potential advancement
create example prototype and demonstration and documenting intellectual property
basic qualifications
master's degree or higher from an accredited institution
minimum of three 3 year of data analytics experience eg predictive modeling statistic machine learning data mining
experience in machine learning and statistical algorithm development
experience in computer or scientific programming
preferred qualifications
phd in data or computer sciences statistics applied math or an engineering discipline
minimum of six 6 year demonstrated expertise in at least two of the following data technology data analysis data mining machine learning data science statistical algorithm development for pattern recognition or predictive model
minimum of five 5 year of expertise in programming in at least one of the following language r python matlab c++ c
minimum of one 1 year of computer vision and image signal processing experience in academia industry or national lab environment
high level of independence and initiative demonstrated ability to identify project opportunity and a proven track record of driving change solution
location woodbury mn
travel may include up to 10 domestic international
relocation benefits are authorized for this position
